</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=belcegaegwynsd>Belce Gaegwyn SD</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/31/01 1:22:03 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.einkaufs.net/service/spiele/diablo/images/warrior1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear Recap.. 3/30</span><hr size=1> I believe their alliance is called Forged Alliance.<br>
<br>
We had a good plan and we had the horses to make the run, unfortunately we lacked the riders on those horses to make it work.  <br>
<br>
Assist not working?  It seemed to work well for the team that helped us get our corpses back.  I know that everyone did use a hot key for this and dutifully clicked it when the target was called out, did those people have a target already selected when they did so?  Were they already in auto attack on that target?  If so next time you get a pull in, target another and attack then assist, it won't change your target.  <br>
<br>
Yep, charming the current target was disturbing.  Great a couple more seconds and this one will be.... charmed. &lt;sigh&gt;  Now we have to switch targets, which with a single group is no problem really, but we have 4 or more to switch targets and that takes time and wastes the effort done on that target and the effort lost due to time taken for the switch.  It also contributed to a loss in confidence in assist working.<br>
<br>
Attacking mezzed MOB's resulted in the death of our crowd control.  No player on a raid like this should be clicking on a MOB and then hitting auto attack, doing so will just release the MOB to seek out the enchanter, most likely jumping over your shoulder and through a crowd.  Don't have a target?  Hit the esc key and then the /assist key, still no target look for the main assist and target, then /assist again.  <br>
<br>
I think that those that went in with the CR team will say is that they did what we had planned.  <br>
<br>
 <p>Belce Gaegwyn                  
Silver Daggers
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukahdius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kahdius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/31/01 2:02:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear Recap.. 3/30</span><hr size=1> Well everyone, although we did have a defeat this time, I think it is an invaluable defeat, for we have learned not to underestimate the new-and-improved Plane of Fear.  <br>
<br>
Dogedme did a great job organizing and briefing everyone but unfortunately we still had people who were not aware of the instructions.  I'm not sure if it was just that everyone is not familiar with the &quot;stand and die&quot; rule, or that we were all overanxious to get things moving but we had lots of people who were training the camp.  I was standing in a safe place between the portal and the camp on the 3rd attempt break in and all further break ins (I didn't hit my hide key quickly enough on the first two and I have the corpses to prove it), and I personally watched many people get aggroed, REALIZE it, and then run to the camp, wiping out our forces.  This is far from acceptable.  If you read the pre-briefing you should know that if you are not on the pull or break in teams, bringing ANYTHING back to the camp is against the rules, and not indicative of an experienced raider.<br>
<br>
The next thing problem we had was assisting.  I know that not only did we sometimes have our primary and secondary assists on different targets, but we also had some charmed targets, some people who got confused during our whole &quot;who's the primary assist&quot; discussion, some people who's hotkeys didn't work properly, and some people apparently not assisting at all.  I would recommend that from now on each of you not familiar with large scale raids, make two hotkeys, one primary, one secondary.  When assisting, wait until you see the message in shout or ooc (whichever is being used, should be shout) by the primary assist calling out the target.  The primary assist should have ALREADY engaged combat BEFORE calling out the target, as the /assist function only works if the person being assisted has auto attack on (there are exceptions to this but for the most part it's the case).<br>
<br>
Other than that I think we had a very good fighting force.  The pull crew, and all other FDers did a great job moving their positions around without dying (despite a few Death Touches by Cazic's little helpers) and otherwise following directions and being patient.  The groups outside from what I heard were also similarly patient despite the long waits.  Of course they did have plenty of drinking to keep them occupied ( I received a number of tells from some absolutely TRASHED raiders trying to tell me some important things only succeeding in making my head hurt from trying to decode what they were saying.)<br>
<br>
You have become better at Drunken Cryptography! (21)<br>
<br>
I also want to say that Dogedme did a very professional job.  Although I have never attended a raid under his leadership before I would gladly do so again.  I hope he does not loose heart.  This defeat reflected in no way upon his leadership abilities, as someone who watched the whole thing from the inside, I can attest to that.  Also, none of you raiders better loose heart either, because next time we go into that plane, we're going to be a tightly balanced, well-tuned killing machine, and those mini-bosses are going to seriously regret all of those Death Touches we received (I'm still sore from mine).<br>
