<br>
As for the hot keys, yes, that probably was a mistake to include that in the briefing. It's becoming obvious to me from these posts that no one hotkey setup is right for everyone. The assist key should be set up to match the players ability, experience and apparently even system to some extent. I used the setup in the briefing, which I've been using for maybe two weeks now, and I never once had a failed assist the entire evening. If you don't take away anything else from this discussion, please remember the point made about not assisting until after the target has been called. If you assist before the call, it's quite possible you will find a target and engage it. It's equally probable that you will be on the wrong target. Also, work with your assist key outside a large raid environment. Find what works for you, and when you join the raid, use the setup that you are certain will put you on the correct target absolutely every time. There's no reason all the hotkeys have to be the same.... what's important is that the end result is the same.<br>
